title: Four Great Americans: Washington, Franklin, Webster, Lincoln. A Book for Young Americans
creator: James Baldwim
description: LibriVox recording of Four Great Americans: Washington, Franklin, Webster, Lincoln, by James Baldwin. Read by Sibella Denton. Written for children, James Baldwin's history of Washington, Franklin, Webster, and Lincoln brings these men to life in a way that will be interesting for adults as well. The stories touch on the little humanities of the great men, rather than dwelling on the great works and great events of their lifetimes, without ignoring the latter. (Summary written by Sibella Denton) For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. M4B format available
